---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { nenaBoardOfficers } from '../data/board-officers';
import { getMailchimpSignupUrl } from '../utils/mailchimp';

const mailchimpUrl = getMailchimpSignupUrl();
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const bylawsPdfUrl = `${base}documents/migrated/nenabozeman-org/NENA%20BYLAWS%202024.pdf`;
---

<Base
  title="Governance"
  description="NENA bylaws, board elections, officer roles, and how we run the Northeast Neighborhood Association."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">Governance</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-green max-w-none mb-10">
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        How NENA operates—membership, meetings, the board, and elections—is documented in our bylaws and summarized below.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mt-8 mb-3" id="bylaws">Bylaws</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
        NENA's bylaws describe membership, meetings, elections, and how the board operates.
      </p>
      <p class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-2 sm:gap-4">
        <a href={`${base}governance/bylaws`} class="text-accent hover:text-amber-700 font-medium">Full bylaws (on this site)</a>
        <span class="hidden sm:inline text-gray-400" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
        <a href={bylawsPdfUrl} class="text-accent hover:text-amber-700 font-medium" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          NENA Bylaws 2024 (PDF)
        </a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mt-8 mb-3" id="elections">Elections and leadership</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        NENA is led by volunteer officers elected by neighborhood members. Details below are carried forward from the prior
        nenabozeman.org elections page; the{' '}
        <a href={bylawsPdfUrl} class="text-accent hover:text-amber-700 font-medium" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          NENA Bylaws 2024 (PDF)
        </a>{' '}
        is authoritative if anything differs.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-primary mt-6 mb-2" id="election-schedule">Election schedule</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        Officer terms are staggered so not all four offices are up in the same year. The prior site described it this way: in
        one cycle (in even-numbered years) members elect a <strong>President</strong> and <strong>Vice President</strong>; in
        the other two-year cycle they elect a <strong>Secretary</strong> and <strong>Treasurer</strong>. See the{' '}
        <a href={bylawsPdfUrl} class="text-accent hover:text-amber-700 font-medium" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          bylaws
        </a>{' '}
        for the exact terms and procedures.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-primary mt-6 mb-2" id="current-officers">Current officers</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 not-prose my-4 max-w-2xl">
        {nenaBoardOfficers.map((member) => (
          <div class="bg-cream rounded-lg p-4 border border-amber-100">
            <p class="font-semibold text-primary">{member.name}</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">{member.role}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-primary mt-6 mb-2" id="article-vi">Officer roles (from the bylaws)</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">
        Excerpt from <strong>Article VI: Leadership structure</strong> in the bylaws (see PDF for full text and
        cross-references such as Article VIII).
      </p>
      <ol class="text-gray-700 list-decimal pl-5 space-y-3">
        <li>
          The NENA’s leadership structure consists of four elected officers. The “regular” work of the NENA is carried out
          by the elected officers—President, Vice President, Secretary, and Treasurer. “Regular” work includes, but is not
          limited to, planning and organizing bi-annual meetings, meeting with the City and other parties as appropriate,
          coordinating with neighborhood committees, and coordinating the development, publication, and distribution of a
          neighborhood newsletter. The President, Vice President, or designated representative shall attend monthly
          Inter-Neighborhood Council (INC) meetings on behalf of the NENA.
        </li>
        <li>
          The President is the primary contact for the NENA. If the President is unavailable, the Vice President is the
          primary contact, then the Secretary, then the Treasurer. All officers are subject to Article VIII, section 5 before
          making decisions on behalf of the NENA.
        </li>
        <li>
          The Secretary is required to attend both regularly scheduled NENA meetings and special, topical NENA meetings, and
          is the sole person responsible for recording and making the meeting minutes available as a public record. The
          Secretary may request help completing these tasks.
        </li>
        <li>
          The Treasurer shall provide a report on the NENA’s financial status at the regularly scheduled fall and spring NENA
          meetings.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-primary mt-6 mb-2" id="financials">NENA financials</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        The NENA President and Treasurer are authorized to sign for the NENA checking account.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-primary mt-6 mb-2" id="how-elections">Nominations, voting, and terms</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        When elections are called (typically in connection with the annual meeting), eligibility, notice, nominations, ballots,
        and terms are all governed by the{' '}
        <a href={bylawsPdfUrl} class="text-accent hover:text-amber-700 font-medium" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          bylaws
        </a>
        .
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-primary mt-6 mb-2">Member accounts on the legacy site</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        The old site offered <strong>Register</strong> and <strong>Login</strong> for member profiles. The new site uses
        Mailchimp for member profiles and email lists.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-cream rounded-lg p-8 border border-amber-100 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-primary">Stay informed</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
        Election announcements historically appeared under <strong>News</strong> and <strong>Events</strong>. Subscribe for
        reminders.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a
          href={mailchimpUrl}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="bg-accent hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm"
        >
          Newsletter signup
        </a>
        <a
          href={`${base}news`}
          class="border border-primary text-primary font-semibold px-5 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm"
        >
          News
        </a>
        <a
          href={`${base}events`}
          class="border border-primary text-primary font-semibold px-5 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm"
        >
          Events
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
